author_ssm: Lisa Darms.  Additional processing by Julianna Monjeau and Connor Gaudet.
abstract_ssm: The Ernest G. Sihler Papers consist of notebooks and other materials generated by Classicist and New York University Latin Professor Ernest G. Sihler (1853-1942). The collection is made up primarily of notebooks containing handwritten notes on Classical subjects made to augment Sihler's scholarship and teaching; the notebooks are often written in a combination of English, Latin, and Ancient Greek, and his earliest student notebooks are in German. The collection also contains manuscripts and a small amount of correspondence.
